Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.06,0:01:39.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like he's settled down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.39,0:02:08.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So...what are we\Ngoing to do about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.23,0:02:21.24,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 19\NEscape
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.21,0:02:25.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can hardly believe that\NShin-Yogo's second prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.17,0:02:27.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...would end up being\Nthe Nyunga Ro Chaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.04,0:02:32.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you like, we can protect him\Nhere in the village until spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.12,0:02:35.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Certain circumstances won't\Nallow us to accept your offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.15,0:02:40.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?\NLook at what I did to the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.76,0:02:43.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:46.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It happened because\Nwe were careless, not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.86,0:02:50.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's asleep. It looks like the\Nshock has started to wear off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.53,0:02:51.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.31,0:03:00.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nimka, please tell us\Nthe rest of that story.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.44,0:03:05.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We already knew that the\Negg-eater would be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.31,0:03:08.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The reason we\Nhadn't told him anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.58,0:03:13.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...was that we'd intended to do it after\Nwe'd found a way to drive it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.36,0:03:14.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.53,0:03:22.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You said that the egg-eater\Ncouldn't be seen or touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.60,0:03:24.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.47,0:03:27.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.\NThat's just what I was taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.84,0:03:30.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But she said that it\Nwas clearly visible when...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.67,0:03:33.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it was tearing the\NNyunga Ro Chaga apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.84,0:03:37.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They said they saw many claws\Ncoming out of the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:40.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Many claws?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.68,0:03:43.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like trouble,\Nwhatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.82,0:03:48.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nimka, did your great-grandmother\Ntell you anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.76,0:03:52.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the egg-eater\Ndidn't like, for instance?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.90,0:03:55.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not surprising...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.07,0:03:59.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they knew anything, they would\Nhave tried it a hundred years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.80,0:04:06.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I wish I had something\Nencouraging to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.78,0:04:10.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but she said that the Nyunga Ro\NChaga is destined to be devoured by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.38,0:04:18.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it seems that the\NYona Ro Gai spoke the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.99,0:04:21.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if it ate him, egg and all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.46,0:04:26.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...we wouldn't have been blessed\Nwith water like we have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:29.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That means that the egg\Nhatched safely a century ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:31.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So why not the\NNyunga Ro Chaga also?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.51,0:04:40.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think... the Nyunga Ro Chaga can\Nonly deposit the egg here in Sagu...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.04,0:04:42.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...by being ripped open by Rarunga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.78,0:04:45.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The say that Nyunga Ro Im\Nis a spirit born in Sagu's oceans...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.52,0:04:50.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that makes its way upriver, and lives\Nat the bottom of Nayug's deep waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.15,0:04:54.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's necessary for\Nthe egg to be deposited here first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.69,0:04:57.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe this egg-eater Rarunga...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.29,0:05:01.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is one of the forces of nature that\Nallows Sagu and Nayug to interact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.90,0:05:06.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, how does the egg travel\Nfrom the headwaters of the Aoyumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.04,0:05:08.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...all the way to the sea\Nonce it's deposited here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.10,0:05:10.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does it travel down\Nthe river on its own?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:12.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's like it says in\Nthe rice-planting song.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:15.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A nahji bird picks up the egg\Nin its beak and carries it to sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.71,0:05:19.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rice-planting song?\NThe one that goes "Nahji, fly, fly"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.65,0:05:23.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The third verse of the song goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.49,0:05:28.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,..."Go, nahji, go, take the ball in your\Nbeak and fly up above the claws," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.16,0:05:31.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did the lyrics really say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.40,0:05:36.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That verse isn't sung much\Naround Yogo farm villages any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.27,0:05:39.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,People thought it was a bit vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.17,0:05:41.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that is certainly how we\Nused to sing it back in the old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.84,0:05:48.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So the line "If you fly to the sea, the\Nrains will fall and the seedlings will grow"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.91,0:05:51.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...was actually the\Nfourth verse, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.11,0:05:54.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Taken as a whole, it could mean that\Na nahji will rescue Nyunga Ro lm's egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.82,0:05:57.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...from the egg-eater's claws\Nand carry it to the sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.65,0:06:00.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...where it will grow into\Na spirit and cause rain to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.16,0:06:06.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of all the luck... That just leaves us\Nwith an even bigger problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.43,0:06:08.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The nahji!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.90,0:06:13.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You people are\Nso slow to catch on...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.40,0:06:16.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When was the last time\Nany of you saw a nahji?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.31,0:06:18.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.91,0:06:24.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I used to see the sky filled\Nwith nahji as they flew south.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.68,0:06:26.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.25,0:06:30.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They've become even rarer\Nsince Yogo started working steel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.55,0:06:34.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even bones for charms against evil\Nspirits are hard to come by these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:37.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate,\Nwe might not be able to...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.83,0:06:42.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...carry the water spirit safely to\Nthe sea, let alone protect the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.53,0:06:46.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we lost more\Nin the past hundred years...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.34,0:06:50.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...than just our customs\Nand oral traditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.29,0:07:03.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.52,0:07:07.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Taga? Where is Master Shuga?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.49,0:07:10.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He is about six nan\Naway from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.09,0:07:13.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, we should reach\NToumi sometime before noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.83,0:07:17.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Master Shuga appears tired,\Nbut he should make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.60,0:07:21.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jin, travel on ahead to Toumi\Nand scout the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.60,0:07:22.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:24.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Taga, Sune. Go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.81,0:07:25.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.68,0:07:33.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, we'll be in the\Nmain house across the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.77,0:07:58.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Balsa...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.87,0:08:03.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not even you can fight\Nsomething that you can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.25,0:08:09.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, if Chagum has to be killed for\Nthe egg to be deposited here in Sagu...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.75,0:08:11.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...we should just run\Nsomeplace far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.55,0:08:14.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't. Even if\Nwe run from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:17.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there's no escaping the destiny\Nhe's been burdened with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.46,0:08:20.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not unless we fight\Nto find another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.73,0:08:24.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I gave my word\Nthat I wouldn't let him die.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.83,0:08:26.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do whatever it takes to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.20,0:08:29.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai, can you think of anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.41,0:08:34.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Some way to both save Chagum and\Nallow the water spirit's egg to hatch?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.08,0:08:38.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.95,0:08:43.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, we still have\Nsome time before spring comes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.05,0:08:45.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so let's come up\Nwith something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.02,0:08:48.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if the palace\Nhas sent out pursuers...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.26,0:08:50.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...we can't assume\Nthat we'll be safe here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.53,0:08:53.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We should move somewhere\Nelse as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.20,0:08:56.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How about Hunter's Hole, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.63,0:09:02.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea. We might be able to\Nprepare for things if we go there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.19,0:09:27.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I'm sorry about earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.90,0:09:30.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean to tell you\Nsuch a terrible story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:34.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's all right.\NIf you hadn't told us the story then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.74,0:09:37.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I'd still be completely in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:40.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's allowed me to\Nmake up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.34,0:09:45.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going back to the palace\Nby myself. Back to my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.68,0:09:51.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The spirit's egg has made me suffer\None terrible ordeal after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.42,0:09:54.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take it any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:58.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.56,0:10:03.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.50,0:10:06.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's no wonder that you're scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:11.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you are the guardian of the spirit,\NI'm sure you don't want to be eaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.37,0:10:15.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll take you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.17,0:10:41.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do? Infiltrate the\Nvillage and get confirmation?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.44,0:10:43.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, people will come out to\Nthe fields once the sun comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.94,0:10:46.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When they do, we'll ask them\Nabout the goings-on in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.14,0:10:48.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want to alert the\Nspear-wielder to our presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.84,0:11:17.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga, we've\Nbeen awaiting your arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.34,0:11:21.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've sent Jin and others on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.94,0:11:25.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please get some rest now,\Nand we'll set out at dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.75,0:11:27.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.48,0:11:30.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I doubt there'll be\Nmuch time for rest...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.40,0:11:42.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.83,0:11:46.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is Nimka still with\Nyou in your quarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.54,0:11:51.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nimka? I think she and the headman\Nwent back to the main house last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.41,0:11:57.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I checked on her earlier, it\Nlooked like her bed hadn't been slept in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.21,0:12:01.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that perhaps she was telling\Nyou more of the stories that she knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:18.00,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.30,0:12:25.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only the people of Toumi\Nknow about this path.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:29.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we follow this, we can reach\Nthe Yashiro village area in two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.03,0:12:52.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. Those two left the\Nvillage, and we had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.80,0:12:57.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the area is like Nimka's backyard,\Nso I'm not worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.37,0:13:00.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if anything happens\Nto the Nyunga Ro Chaga...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.94,0:13:04.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you figure out\Nwhen they left?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:08.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a man said that he noticed\Nthe dogs barking at daybreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.08,0:13:10.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been\Nsometime around then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:15.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa is out looking for them...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.09,0:13:18.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so I expect she'll bring\Nthem back soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.39,0:13:20.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As for us, we need to\Nget ready to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.44,0:13:30.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nice day, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.14,0:13:39.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry if I startled you,\Nbut I'd like to ask you some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.01,0:13:43.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that an outlander woman\Nand a Yogo boy are visiting the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.65,0:13:44.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where\NI might find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.92,0:13:48.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they're staying at\Nthe village headman's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.49,0:13:51.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the furthest building\Nfrom the village entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:52.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be able to tell\Nwhich one it is right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.93,0:13:57.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see. There wasn't anyone else\Ntravelling with them, was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.17,0:14:02.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There was a Yakoo man and a magic\Nweaver who looked like his grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.34,0:14:06.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But they were talking about possibly\Nleaving the village this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.24,0:14:09.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so they might have left for\Nwherever they were headed already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:21.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This grandmother you mentioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.62,0:14:25.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...was she an old woman about\Nthis tall carrying a strange staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.73,0:14:28.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.73,0:14:31.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, we should hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.72,0:14:55.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.20,0:15:10.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For a moment, it was like I was\Nsomehow looking on a different landscape...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.37,0:15:12.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.69,0:15:24.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:31.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, we're going\Nback to the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.70,0:15:35.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.23,0:15:39.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you keep\Neverything from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:43.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About the egg-eater...\NAbout me dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:44.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You knew all along, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.44,0:15:48.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.91,0:15:51.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I kept it\Nfrom you until now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.45,0:15:53.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is because we didn't\Nknow anything for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.22,0:15:56.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to\Nworry you needlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.79,0:15:57.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.29,0:16:02.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The egg is more important\Nto you than I am, Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.49,0:16:04.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.23,0:16:09.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You and the egg are both precious\Nthings that deserve to be protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.87,0:16:11.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Deserve to be protected?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.97,0:16:19.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, you don't need to\Nworry about me any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.18,0:16:21.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm returning to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.95,0:16:26.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't my mother,\Nso you can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.92,0:16:30.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have no idea how\NI'm suffering, so you don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.46,0:16:43.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. If you want to\Ngo back that badly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.44,0:16:57.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Use that to kill me first.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.82,0:17:08.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once I've set my mind to do something,\Nnothing can make me budge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.39,0:17:10.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you go\Nback to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.43,0:17:13.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you insist on going\Nanyway, pick that up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.55,0:17:37.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.62,0:17:39.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, run me through with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.53,0:17:50.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, no matter\Nhow tough you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:17:53.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...you're no match for some\Nmonster with gigantic claws!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.17,0:17:57.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going back to the palace to have\NShuga and my mother protect me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.00,0:18:24.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you raise a weapon\Nagainst your parent!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.98,0:18:39.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're all trying our hardest\Nto protect you, Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.55,0:18:42.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What were you thinking,\Nrunning off on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.82,0:18:44.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll protect you no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.15,0:18:48.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, you're the\Nguardian of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.02,0:18:50.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So even if you're scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.79,0:18:54.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...you have to keep fighting to\Nthe bitter end to protect the egg!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.33,0:19:00.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it costs me my life,\NI won't let you die!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.44,0:19:04.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So please, I'm asking\Nyou to have faith in me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:09.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.61,0:19:12.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why does it have to be me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.54,0:19:44.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is the village headman here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.28,0:19:48.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We believe the second prince of the\NShin-Yogo empire is in this village!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.02,0:19:53.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are envoys of the mikado sent\Nhere from Kosenkyo to retrieve him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.69,0:19:56.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We request an immediate audience!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.13,0:20:01.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be faster\Nto follow this river?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:04.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but if we take the\Nprince into consideration...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.97,0:20:08.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...a slightly more level route\Nwould probably be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.10,0:20:10.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.97,0:20:12.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Soya!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.04,0:20:16.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A man with warriors in the square\Nsays they've been sent by the palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.28,0:20:18.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He says they've\Ncome for the prince!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.51,0:20:19.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.55,0:20:22.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We slipped up...\NThey're here already?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.99,0:20:29.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go and hear what\Nthey have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.09,0:20:34.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You hide yourselves and wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.04,0:20:45.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodness gracious, what a treat\Nto have visitors from so far away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.94,0:20:47.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the village headman?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.68,0:20:50.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I have that honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.21,0:20:54.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good, that simplifies matters.\NBring out the prince at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.08,0:20:57.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I'm afraid I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.99,0:20:59.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.26,0:21:05.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You see, just as he is\Nprecious to you as your prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.99,0:21:09.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to us Yakoo, he is also\Nthe guardian of the spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.00,0:21:13.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...he who nurtures the\Nprotector of the water within him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.57,0:21:16.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the egg he bears\Nwithin him fails to hatch...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.30,0:21:20.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...these lands will never again\Nbe blessed with water.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.91,0:21:24.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you see, this is why\Nwe can't bring him to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.51,0:21:27.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are also aware of these facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.25,0:21:29.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As such, none of us\Nwishes him any harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.89,0:21:33.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary, we are here so that\Nwe may keep him safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.82,0:21:37.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My people cannot live without\Nthe blessings of water, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.26,0:21:42.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If your people care at all for\Nthis land, or for Shin-Yogo...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.00,0:21:45.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...will you entrust both him\Nand the spirit's egg to our care?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.87,0:21:51.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You speak of country, but that has little\Nbearing on the lives of the people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.51,0:21:53.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we Yakoo\Nhave protected...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.44,0:21:57.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the Nyunga Ro Chaga ourselves\Nfor generation after generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.71,0:22:02.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just as we did when one of our own\Nwas the Nyunga Ro Chaga a century ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.52,0:22:05.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I ask that you allow\Nus Yakoo to see to this...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.22,0:22:08.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bring out the prince while\Nwe're still asking politely.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.59,0:22:11.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, this village\Nwill be wiped off the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.63,0:22:15.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a very civil\Ntone to take, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.07,0:22:25.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spear-wielder! Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.94,0:22:28.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You won't get away\Nlike you did before!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.64,0:22:31.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do everything in our\Npower to bring you down!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.35,0:22:34.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what your motive is,\Ndragging the prince around with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.82,0:22:37.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but your work is done!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.59,0:22:39.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come out peacefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.92,0:22:44.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet, you noisy brats!\NWhat's all this shouting about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.83,0:22:53.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, isn't he...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.90,0:22:57.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am Torogai the magic weaver!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.91,0:23:01.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The prince and the spear-wielder\Nare no longer here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.24,0:23:04.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you have something\Nto say, say it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.28,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.71,0:24:46.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His heart filled with unavoidable\Nemotions, Chagum walks on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.05,0:24:48.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And on... And on...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.12,0:24:52.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "To Hunter's Hole."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 20\NTo Hunter's Hole
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.89,0:24:54.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One man's fate can't be\Nshouldered by another.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.96,0:24:56.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What would you do in his place?
